Computational single-cell biology course

Hakime Öztürk (h.oeztuerk@dkfz-heidelberg.de)

01 June, 2021

HOMEWORK

1. Read the original mouse gastrulation scRNA-seq Seurat object (2GBs) and the meta-data and then subset the data to cell stage = e7.25.

Note: set.seed(1)

2. Reduce the dimensionality of the dataset to 100 with PCA and plot the percentage of explained variance using standard deviation.

3. Use the first 20 PCs to represent the dataset and find clusters with k-means, hclust and Louvain algorithms. Visualize the predicted clusters with tSNE and UMAP. Compare the visualizations to real cell type assignments.

Note:

  • for the algorithms that need number of clusters as input, use k=20.
  • for hierarchical clustering, use manhattan as distance metric and complete as the linkage method.
  • for the algorithms that rely on number of nearest neighbors as input, use k=10.
